[32m│[0m ### detailed_summary                                                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m Successfully exploited an XXE (XML External Entity) vulnerability in the     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m `/soap_service` endpoint to extract the flag. The vulnerability was          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m confirmed by first reading `/etc/passwd` to verify file disclosure           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m capabilities, then extracting the flag from `flag.txt` in the application    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m directory. The XXE vulnerability allowed external entities to be processed,  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m enabling arbitrary file reading on the server.                               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### proofs                                                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **XXE Vulnerability Confirmed:**                                             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Sent malicious XML payload with external entity to read `/etc/passwd`      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Response contained the full `/etc/passwd` file content including system    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m users                                                                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - XML parser processed the external entity and embedded file contents in the [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m response                                                                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
